<title>COLLECT-SUGAR-DELAYED</title>

</head>



<body>



<div id="bodyContent">

	<h3><i>I postpone collecting all the sugar where I am until I'm finished 

	moving.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>COLLECT-SUGAR-DELAYED </b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>do-after .001
   [add-behaviour <a href="COLLECT-SUGAR.html">COLLECT-SUGAR</a>]
</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p>This relies upon

	<a title="COLLECT-SUGAR" href="COLLECT-SUGAR.html">

	COLLECT-SUGAR</a> to do the real work. </p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>It starts the repeating process of collecting sugar .001 time units after 

	the move step. </p>

	<h2>Source</h2>
	<p>Based upon page 24 of [1]. </p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn. </p>

	<h2>References</h2>

	<p>[1] <i>Growing Artificial Societies</i> by Joshua M. Epstein and Robert 

	Axtell, Brookings Institute Press, The MIT Press, 1996. </div>



